      <h2 class="section__heading">A Certified ProAdvisor sets the file up so it ties from day one.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Ticking through a checklist yourself is entirely doable &mdash; that&rsquo;s why this page exists. What a Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor adds is judgment on the parts that quietly decide whether the file stays clean: a chart of accounts shaped to how you actually report, opening balances that reconcile to the bank from the start, the correct cut-over date when you&rsquo;re migrating, and preferences set for your accounting method and sales-tax reality rather than the defaults. A ProAdvisor with active Online and Desktop certifications does that against a written scope and verifies the file ties before handing it over. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not Intuit&rsquo;s software support; an Intuit account, login, or billing matter stays with Intuit.</p>
